WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.420
The first one is that I think there are quite a few cynical people outside of this hall

00:04.420 --> 00:08.700
and thinking, is there any point in having a summit on peace?

00:09.400 --> 00:12.940
And to them, I think the simple answer is to say that, as a matter of fact,

00:13.300 --> 00:16.400
if you don't talk about peace, you can't achieve it.

00:17.200 --> 00:20.520
And the mere fact that we have 60 heads of state government here,

00:20.520 --> 00:25.600
that we have 100 countries, I think is an achievement in and of itself.

00:26.360 --> 00:32.240
And I think for us in the global West, it's very important to listen to the voices that we've heard here.

00:32.400 --> 00:38.400
Today, I've listened attentively to the president of Kenya, president of Ghana and Chile,

00:38.540 --> 00:43.120
prime minister of Qatar, and the foreign minister of South Africa.

00:43.120 --> 00:49.020
There are wars waging around the world, and they call for peace as much as this one.

00:49.820 --> 00:53.420
Now, for those who don't come from next to Russia,

00:53.420 --> 00:56.980
you must also understand that a lot of us are worried.

00:58.220 --> 01:01.500
We have 1,300 kilometers of border with Russia.

01:01.880 --> 01:06.760
Since the 1300s, we've had over 30 wars and skirmishes with Russia.

01:07.500 --> 01:09.660
Russia invaded Finland in World War II.

01:10.500 --> 01:15.120
We lost 10% of our territory, including the land where my grandparents were born

01:15.120 --> 01:17.420
and where my father was born.

01:17.940 --> 01:21.940
This is why the reaction from our side has been so vehement.

01:21.940 --> 01:27.160
My second point is that I actually think this has been a good week for peace.

01:27.540 --> 01:27.740
Why?

01:28.440 --> 01:31.860
Because of this summit, because of the G7 summit,

01:32.580 --> 01:36.380
because the EU negotiations for Ukraine started this week,

01:36.700 --> 01:41.660
and because of the support that our NATO allies are giving to Ukraine.

01:41.660 --> 01:48.340
So I think that Ukraine actually starts this path towards peace from a position of strength

01:48.340 --> 01:53.940
much stronger than what it was three weeks ago, let alone three months ago.

01:53.940 --> 01:58.700
My third and final point is, when we talk about peace,

01:58.700 --> 02:01.400
it's important to talk about the nature of peace.

02:01.900 --> 02:05.700
And here's where I think it's very important to listen to not only President Zelensky,

02:06.380 --> 02:11.500
but all of those who say that this has to be a just and sustainable peace,

02:11.740 --> 02:15.760
which is based on international law and the UN Charter.

02:15.760 --> 02:20.700
It also means that we need to have a follow-up to this meeting as soon as possible,

02:21.120 --> 02:23.620
because peace is very rarely an end state.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.180
It's always a process.

02:26.780 --> 02:31.460
And let me finish off by saying what my predecessor and mentor,

02:32.200 --> 02:34.940
President Ahtisari, once said.

02:35.360 --> 02:37.320
What humans began, begin.

02:37.800 --> 02:39.060
Humans can also end.

02:39.060 --> 02:44.380
So I hope that this summit will be the first step in the path towards peace.

02:44.600 --> 02:45.780
Thank you for the invitation.

02:46.060 --> 02:46.780
And Slav Al-Krej.

